name: S410 Files: Tree
description: First of a series exploring the world as viewed by a naturally glitched camera, a near pristine state Canon PowerShot (Digital ELPH) S410, manufactured February 2004. Today its senescent sensor distorts the image unpredictably, but curiously not every time: it's a matter of pure luck. Must keep shooting with its worn out battery (good for only about 5 shots) and hoping for the defect to come out again. Picture taken 11 July 2013. Originally released on 11 June 2021 as HeN OBJKT 127498.
